citations:
    citation-affc-the-captain-of-guards-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "The Captain of Guards"
            text_from_source: "Obara Sand always walked too fast. She is chasing after something she can never catch, the prince had told his daughter once, in the captain's hearing."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Areo Hotah, Captain of the Guards at the Water Gardens. Chapter title: The Captain of Guards. Prince Doran Martell is at the Water Gardens, in a rolling chair due to severe gout, when Obara Sand arrives with news of Oberyn's death and demands war. Doran then travels by litter to Sunspear, where Nymeria Sand accosts him on the road, and Tyene Sand awaits in the Tower of the Sun. Each Sand Snake proposes a different form of vengeance (Obara: open war on Oldtown; Nym: assassination of Cersei, Jaime, and Joffrey/Tommen; Tyene: crown Myrcella as queen by Dornish succession law). Doran orders Hotah to arrest all three Sand Snakes (plus Ellaria Sand's younger daughters for their safety). Key figures: Maester Caleotte (Doran's maester), Ricasso (old blind seneschal of Sunspear), Ser Manfrey Martell (castellan), Maester Myles, Myrcella Baratheon, Ser Arys Oakheart (Myrcella's Kingsguard escort). Doran reveals Oberyn went to King's Landing as his eyes and ears, not to fight. Establishes the three towers of Sunspear: Spear Tower, Tower of the Sun, Sandship. Doran's gout is extensively described."
